  "title": "RESTAURANT SUPERVISOR/ASST SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Responsible for all aspect of the restaurant operations, accounting, financial and administrative (including personnel) matters.</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>· Manpower Management - able to mentor staff to achieve excellent service for outlets and improve profit margin for the organization.</p><p>· Able to delegate tasks efficiently and fairly among employees and conduct OJT training.</p><p>· Inventory Management - ensure all inventories are well-kept and organized.</p><p>· Responsible for employee performance and discipline.</p><p>· Develop good working relationships with internal and external stakeholders.</p><p>· Manage the Quality, Service, Cleanliness & Value (QSCV) of a restaurant.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Excellent leadership skills - at least 2 years of supervisory experience in the F&B industry especially in managing an outlet.</p><p>· Able to lead and motivate restaurant staff to achieve set objectives.</p><p>· Proficient in Microsoft Office - handle administrative work and reports at the restaurant level.</p><p>· Able to perform the tasks of all roles in the restaurant.</p><p>· Well-groomed and pleasant personality.</p><p>· Aspire to use creativity in the workplace by bringing fresh ideas to improve the outlet workflow.</p><p>· Problem solver and has a passion to think out of the box to achieve the desired outcome.</p><p>· Able to work efficiently under pressure.</p>",
